    android.content.ComponentCallbacks, android.content.ComponentCallbacks2, android.support.v4.app.ActivityCompat.OnRequestPermissionsResultCallback, android.support.v4.app.ActivityCompatApi23.RequestPermissionsRequestCodeValidator, android.support.v4.app.TaskStackBuilder.SupportParentable, android.support.v7.app.ActionBarDrawerToggle.DelegateProvider, android.support.v7.app.AppCompatCallback, android.view.KeyEvent.Callback, android.view.LayoutInflater.Factory, android.view.LayoutInflater.Factory2, android.view.View.OnCreateContextMenuListener, android.view.Window.Callback, BackupOutOfSyncDialogFragment.BackupOutOfSyncDialogListener

    @NotThreadSafe
public final class TrampolineActivity
extends FightClubActivity
    Launcher activity that bounces the user to different paths in the app. These are the paths in which it may go down:

    1. Bounce to Language Selection
    2. Bounce to Confirmation Sent screen (in case needed)
    3. Bounce to Reset Password screen
    4. Bounce to Forgot Password screen
    5. Bounce to login expired dialog
    6. Bounce to the Login
    7. Bounce to New Account created screen
    8. Bounce to OOBE - Profile
    9. Bounce to Units of Measurement
    10. Bounce to Permissions screen
    11. Bounce to App Connection Detail
    12. Bounce to OOBE - Connect to Apps
    13. Bounce to Product Overview
    14. Bounce to OOBE - Wearable Pairing
    15. Bounce to OOBE - Sensors Pairing
    16. Bounce to OOBE - Additional Voice Diagnostics
    17. Bounce to download CUI assets
    18. Bounce to download firmware update
    19. Bounce to OOBE - Coach Intro
    20. Bounce to OOBE - Go Intro
    21. Bounce to Cloud Restore (in case needed)
    22. Bounce to Charging Warning
    23. Bounce to Home

      • shouldShowActionBar

        protected boolean shouldShowActionBar()
        Description copied from class: FightClubActivity
        Determines if a Toolbar should be added to the activity as its ActionBar. It is set to true by default, and is only checked once during FightClubActivity.onCreate(android.os.Bundle).
        Overrides:
        shouldShowActionBar in class FightClubActivity
        Returns:
        true by default. Return false to setup a fullscreen activity.
